description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for something new and exciting within healthcare? Have you ever wondered what it is like to work in a prison? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a skilled clinician with demonstrated exceptional leadership and management skills to take up the position of Clinical Matron for Mental Health at HMP Gartree near Market Harborough&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people who share our values&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are non-judgmental&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are caring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have integrity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We put the patient first&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are committed to team work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are proud to work for the NHS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you share these values ?&lt;strong&gt; If the answer is yes&lt;/strong&gt;, read on …………&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We aren’t&lt;/strong&gt; a hospital in the Prison.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We don’t&lt;/strong&gt; have in-patient beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We do&lt;/strong&gt; operate as a Primary care centre, with some urgent treatment provision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We do&lt;/strong&gt; have mental health nurses, IDD nurses, substance misuse practitioners, physical health nurses, a therapeutic community, GPs, physio, dentist, optician, podiatrist, paramedics and psychiatrist and so on……. over 40 staff in fact !!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And &lt;strong&gt;we do&lt;/strong&gt; have an exciting opportunity to recruit a Band 7 Clinical Matron for our Mental Health team at HMP Gartree, providing a level of care to over 700 men that is at the least equivalent to what they would expect to receive in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HMP Gartree is a category B mens prison located near Foxton just outside Market Harborough. The prison is 15 miles from Leicester, Corby and Kettering and 20 miles from Northampton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthcare delivery in a Category B male prison is never dull or predictable – but it is very rewarding. Every day will bring new challenges and new experiences to you as a qualified professional.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Integrated Mental Health team at HMP Gartree comprises of primary and secondary mental health nurses, IDD nurse, psychology, counselling and psychiatrist provision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mental Health team provide a stepped model approach to care provision and cover all aspects and diagnosis of mental illness. We are fully adherent to the CPA guidelines and have an overview of all psychological and pharmacological aspects of care for all patients from triage to recovery. The team provides 1:1 care and case management and group work. The model of delivery is soon to become a 7 day service although this post will be Monday to Friday 8am to 4pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for providing clinical and managerial leadership to a high standard, promoting best practice and developing Mental Healthcare services to enhance quality and improve patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be working alongside the Clinical Matrons for Substance Misuse and Physical Care and other healthcare professionals in the wider healthcare team you’ll have all the support you need to deliver the best care possible to our patients at HMP Gartree&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Want to know more ?&lt;/strong&gt; Come and pay us a visit – and see the world of prison healthcare for yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Bev Bradshaw– Head of Healthcare Bev.Bradshaw@nottshc.nhs.uk for more information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And now for the background info………..Nottinghamshire Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust Offender Health Directorate is one of the largest and most successful providers of prison healthcare in the UK. The Directorate provides physical, mental health and substance misuse healthcare services to a prison population of over 10 000 in prisons across the East Midlands, Lincolnshire and Leicestershire including different categories of prison.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to working in partnership with prison services, other healthcare providers and our criminal justice system partners to improve health, support justice and reduce re-offending behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Offender Health Team truly believes it can make a difference to the lives of offenders by offering consistent, equitable, high quality and timely primary care, mental health and substance misuse services that are at least equivalent to contemporary health services delivered outside of Prison. We would like you to be part of this team; You should be enthusiastic, motivated patient focused and enjoy a challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be an experienced RMN/IDD nurse - and if a non-medical prescriber all the better. The healthcare team operates in a supportive environment with a commitment to personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our DBS check is free, you have no fees to pay!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parking is free&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;on site at HMP Gartree&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBev BradshawJob titleHead of HealthcareEmail addressbev.bradshaw@nottshc.nhs.ukTelephone number01858 426802Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
